This is CCZE, a fast log colorizer written in C, intended to be a
drop-in replacement for colorize (http://colorize.raszi.hu).

See the NEWS file for a description of recent changes to CCZE.

See the file INSTALL for instructions on how to build and install the
CCZE data and program files. See the CCZE manual for details about
configuration. Type "man ccze" in the shell prompt.

Please visit the official CCZE web page for more information. The URL
is http://bonehunter.rulez.org/CCZE.html.


-------------------------------------------------------------------------
ccze-go
-------------------------------------------------------------------------

ccze-go is a Go port of CCZE. By default it is byte-for-byte ANSI
compatible with the C ccze it ports (the test suite enforces this), so
it drops straight into existing pipelines:

    tail -f /var/log/syslog | ccze-go -A

In addition it offers a set of OPT-IN "modern log" highlighters for the
kinds of logs C ccze never targeted (structured/slog output, build and
application logs, etc.). They are all OFF by default and are enabled via
the -o option (comma-separated, with "no"-prefixed variants to disable):

    -o modern       turn on all four stable highlighters below at once
    -o tags         color [INFO]/[WARN]/[ERROR]/[component] bracket tags,
                    with log levels colored by severity
    -o files        color filenames and paths (main.go, src/app.py,
                    ./conf.yaml, /var/log/app.log)
    -o slog         color logfmt / slog key=value pairs (the key is
                    highlighted and the value is colored by its type)
    -o durations    color Go-style durations (30.2s, 1m30s, 100ms, 1.5h)
    -o adaptive     adaptive recurring-structure recognition: learns the
                    stream's recurring delimited shape (|, comma or TAB
                    columns) and gives columns and recurring keys stable,
                    distinct colors so structure pops

Example:

    kubectl logs deploy/app | ccze-go -A -o modern
    cat events.csv         | ccze-go -A -o adaptive

Defaults can be set once via the CCZE_OPTIONS environment variable, which
takes the same comma-separated option string as -o. Set it to make a mode
the default without typing -o every time:

    export CCZE_OPTIONS=modern        # default to the modern highlighters
    tail -f app.log | ccze-go -A      # uses modern automatically

-o is applied on top of CCZE_OPTIONS and overrides it, so you can still
turn individual options off per invocation:

    CCZE_OPTIONS=modern ccze-go -A -o noslog,adaptive < app.log

GUARANTEE: every highlighter only ADDS color. For any input line the
output with all ANSI escape sequences stripped is byte-for-byte identical
to the input -- nothing is ever reordered, dropped, truncated, padded, or
realigned. This is verified by the test suite (including the adaptive
layer) across an adversarial corpus and every flag combination.

Build/test with the go-toolchain:

    go-toolchain
